# 1. Navigate to your project root
cd Week_05_Python_Programming
# or
cd aws_restart

# 2. Create the LICENSE file
touch LICENSE

# 3. Open it in your text editor
code LICENSE
# or
nano LICENSE
# or
vim LICENSE
```

**Your folder structure should look like:**
```
Week_05_Python_Programming/
├── LICENSE                    ← Add it here (root level)
├── README.md
├── Hello-world.py
├── caesar.py
├── analyze-insulin.py
└── ... (all other files)
```

**4. Paste this content into the LICENSE file:**
```
